Cell["\<\
The first term in h/c expansion found in Caputa et al. corresponds to term \
proportional to h, which is our universal term or type-1 term. The type 1 \
area (due to both rr and r\[CurlyPhi]  component of perturbed metric) we \
obtain should match with the corresponding expression. We show this below.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.988609451962234*^9, 3.988609522535862*^9}, {
  3.9886096276766167`*^9, 
  3.988609677138006*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ee46cd4b-0037-446b-a222-\
d9d512d78438"],

